cc:Work.dc:title: Binomial Trees
cc:Work.dc:description: Definition of binomial tree: 1) Binomial tree of order 0 is a single node. 2) Binomial tree of higher order has a root node with subtrees consisting of all binomial trees of lower order. In this diagram, binomial trees of order 0 to 3 are shown, with their subtrees highlighted: subtrees of different order have different highlight colours. Made using Inkscape at http://www.inkscape.org/ only.
